Former Dimension Data CEO Brett Dawson has joined the board of Ubusha Technology. The move follows Dawson leaving Dimension Data in 2016 and joining Free2Cycle as chairman in 2017. Ubusha Technology is an African ICT company that offers cybersecurity, identity governance, and access management solutions to the private and public sectors. “Brett will offer strategic input to the firm and play an advisory role in building, guiding, and nurturing the management team, which is led by Ubusha CEO Marius Agenbag,” stated the company. “Ubusha is a market leader in this vital segment of the IT security market. There are tremendous opportunities to grow in the corporate segment by offering bulletproof solutions that both protect and prevent unauthorised access to corporations’ information assets,” said Dawson.